00:34:00.360 --> 00:34:01.920
<v ->I was taking pictures of children,</v>

786
00:34:01.920 --> 00:34:04.410
boys with sacks of food,

787
00:34:04.410 --> 00:34:06.958
and they would come and fill their sacks up,

788
00:34:06.958 --> 00:34:09.240
take 'em home, empty their sacks,

789
00:34:09.240 --> 00:34:11.369
and come back for another sack of food.

790
00:34:11.369 --> 00:34:14.318
Well, it took

791
00:34:15.238 --> 00:34:18.869
several hours for all this to penetrate my mind,

792
00:34:18.869 --> 00:34:21.720
you know, as everybody began to share.

793
00:34:23.050 --> 00:34:24.930
<v Voiceover>Father Thomas stopped keeping count</v>

794
00:34:24.930 --> 00:34:27.480
when the crowd surpassed 400 people

795
00:34:27.480 --> 00:34:29.340
who came for the Christmas meal

796
00:34:29.340 --> 00:34:31.840
originally planned to feed 120.

797
00:34:33.630 --> 00:34:36.088
<v ->It didn't occur to us until after we had come back</v>

798
00:34:36.088 --> 00:34:37.800
of the miracle that had happened,

799
00:34:37.800 --> 00:34:40.050
because we knew what he had taken across,

800
00:34:40.050 --> 00:34:41.908
and we knew what we had given,

801
00:34:41.908 --> 00:34:43.140
we saw with our own eyes

802
00:34:43.140 --> 00:34:44.700
all the people that were there.

803
00:34:44.700 --> 00:34:46.170
And we saw what was left over after

804
00:34:46.170 --> 00:34:47.700
everybody had gone home.

805
00:34:47.700 --> 00:34:49.289
Where we even had enough to go take down

806
00:34:49.289 --> 00:34:51.168
to the orphanage, that was truly

807
00:34:51.168 --> 00:34:53.428
a wonderful wonderful thing.

808
00:34:53.428 --> 00:34:55.458
<v ->We stopped on the way back to El Paso</v>

809
00:34:55.458 --> 00:34:59.852
at an orphanage in Juarez and left the food there.

810
00:34:59.852 --> 00:35:03.016
I found out a long time later

811
00:35:03.016 --> 00:35:07.252
that a person from Juarez had food left over

812
00:35:07.252 --> 00:35:09.504
and they had stopped at another orphanage

813
00:35:09.504 --> 00:35:12.454
to leave the food that was left over.

814
00:35:13.072 --> 00:35:14.694
And this really got our attention,

815
00:35:14.694 --> 00:35:17.064
and we said, "Well if God multiplied that food,

816
00:35:17.864 --> 00:35:19.410
"that's a sign that we have to go back

817
00:35:19.410 --> 00:35:21.240
"and help those people."

818
00:35:21.240 --> 00:35:22.289
And so that was the beginning

819
00:35:22.289 --> 00:35:24.420
of a ministry at the garbage dump

820
00:35:24.420 --> 00:35:27.240
that's gone on even to this day.

821
00:35:27.240 --> 00:35:32.240
(gentle music)

822
00:35:32.969 --> 00:35:34.560
<v Frank>Yeah over there, that's a cut away of</v>

823
00:35:34.560 --> 00:35:36.330
what they're all living on top of,

824
00:35:36.330 --> 00:35:37.950
that's what the garbage,

825
00:35:37.950 --> 00:35:39.870
the old garbage, that's been there for years

826
00:35:39.870 --> 00:35:42.029
and they just built on top of the garbage.

827
00:35:42.029 --> 00:35:43.380
They haven't got any running water.

828
00:35:43.380 --> 00:35:46.020
But they got barrels here.

829
00:35:46.657 --> 00:35:49.247
If you can see all of these homes right here

830
00:35:49.247 --> 00:35:51.528
and off in the distance, way in the distance,

831
00:35:51.528 --> 00:35:53.816
you see the United States of America.

832
00:35:54.286 --> 00:35:55.786
30 minutes from right here

833
00:35:55.786 --> 00:35:58.068
to the wealthiest nation in the world,

834
00:35:58.068 --> 00:35:59.453
they have all of this.

835
00:35:59.453 --> 00:36:01.043
<v Voiceover>Frank Alarcon was so touched</v>

836
00:36:01.043 --> 00:36:03.025
by what he saw happen that day,

837
00:36:03.025 --> 00:36:05.425
he took it as a sign that he should stay

838
00:36:05.425 --> 00:36:08.615
in Juarez and help the poor people in that town.

839
00:36:08.993 --> 00:36:10.735
<v ->That evening when I went home,</v>

840
00:36:10.735 --> 00:36:12.985
and I went in my room and I closed the door

841
00:36:12.985 --> 00:36:14.854
and on my knees I begged God for a job,

842
00:36:14.854 --> 00:36:17.672
with tears in my eyes, I was so in love

843
00:36:17.672 --> 00:36:19.634
that, I was so in love.

844
00:36:20.224 --> 00:36:22.054
<v Voiceover>He left behind a comfortable retirement</v>

845
00:36:22.054 --> 00:36:24.542
in the US, and organized a daycare,

846
00:36:24.542 --> 00:36:26.884
a doctor's and dentist office,

847
00:36:26.884 --> 00:36:28.354
and other services.

848
00:36:28.354 --> 00:36:30.484
<v ->That's your pharmacy over there.</v>

849
00:36:30.484 --> 00:36:32.432
We charge 10 pesos a visit,

850
00:36:32.432 --> 00:36:34.294
and we give them the medicines

851
00:36:34.294 --> 00:36:35.944
if we have them, if we don't,

852
00:36:35.944 --> 00:36:37.924
then the doctor will make out a prescription for them

853
00:36:37.924 --> 00:36:40.052
to buy, if they don't have the money, fine,

854
00:36:40.052 --> 00:36:42.214
if they don't then we'll buy it for them.

855
00:36:42.214 --> 00:36:44.312
And the same way with the dentist,

856
00:36:44.312 --> 00:36:45.549
if they have the money, if they don't

857
00:36:45.549 --> 00:36:47.351
they still get treatment.

858
00:36:47.351 --> 00:36:48.318
See the white building

859
00:36:48.318 --> 00:36:49.733
with all those barrels on top?

860
00:36:49.733 --> 00:36:51.743
I have a little room in back of there.

861
00:36:51.743 --> 00:36:53.483
<v Voiceover>He now lives in a one room dwelling</v>

862
00:36:53.483 --> 00:36:55.705
with a single light bulb, and a mattress

863
00:36:55.705 --> 00:36:57.056
on a dirt floor.

864
00:36:57.056 --> 00:36:58.865
<v ->Super room.</v>

865
00:36:59.605 --> 00:37:02.155
This is where we celebrated Christmas 1972,

866
00:37:02.155 --> 00:37:03.625
right here.

867
00:37:03.625 --> 00:37:05.903
And it was just a beautiful wonderful day.

868
00:37:05.903 --> 00:37:09.145
I couldn't, I thank God for that Christmas,

869
00:37:09.145 --> 00:37:11.913
it changed my life.

870
00:37:12.263 --> 00:37:13.825
I can't take any credit for anything,

871
00:37:13.825 --> 00:37:15.476
I dare not take credit for anything,

872
00:37:15.476 --> 00:37:18.685
because I'm not capable of those things.

873
00:37:18.685 --> 00:37:20.615
These are just wonders that God has done.

874
00:37:22.225 --> 00:37:24.083
<v Voiceover>When our film crew went out to investigate</v>

875
00:37:24.083 --> 00:37:25.913
these stories at the Lord's Ranch,

876
00:37:25.913 --> 00:37:28.812
they were greeted by something quite unexpected.

877
00:37:29.220 --> 00:37:31.922
<v ->We just arrived here, and I told our cameraman</v>

878
00:37:31.922 --> 00:37:34.832
that we needed to shoot a dark sky

879
00:37:34.832 --> 00:37:36.182
because when we get home,

880
00:37:36.182 --> 00:37:39.120 line:15% 
I'm planning to superimpose a rainbow for an effect,

881
00:37:39.120 --> 00:37:42.182 line:15% 
and not 30 seconds later,

882
00:37:42.182 --> 00:37:46.080
we turned and saw this most beautiful double rainbow

883
00:37:46.080 --> 00:37:47.862
I've ever seen in my life.

884
00:37:48.362 --> 00:37:51.422
<v ->This is a sign that the Lord has given you</v>

885
00:37:51.422 --> 00:37:54.192
to show you what he does here.

886
00:37:54.450 --> 00:37:56.552
He performs miracles here,

887
00:37:56.552 --> 00:37:58.431
and this is His sign to you.

888
00:37:58.431 --> 00:38:00.181
That rainbow.

889
00:38:01.759 --> 00:38:02.971
(mumbles)

890
00:38:03.919 --> 00:38:08.699
(gentle music)

891
00:38:09.711 --> 00:38:14.101
(calm organ)

892
00:38:14.811 --> 00:38:19.471
(suspenseful music)

893
00:38:37.540 --> 00:38:39.398
<v ->Richard Musielak's son Paul</v>

894
00:38:39.398 --> 00:38:42.790
was caught in a mugging situation,

895
00:38:42.790 --> 00:38:44.768 line:15% 
and he was beaten very badly,

896
00:38:44.768 --> 00:38:46.728 line:15% 
Richard got the call that night that

897
00:38:47.689 --> 00:38:50.389 line:15% 
Paul was in the hospital with terrible damage

898
00:38:50.389 --> 00:38:52.037
to his head and face.

899
00:38:52.037 --> 00:38:54.739 line:15% 
<v ->I could not believe what I saw.</v>

900
00:38:56.349 --> 00:38:59.299 line:15% 
His eyes were bleeding, they were

901
00:39:00.449 --> 00:39:02.844
so swollen shut and so swollen

902
00:39:02.844 --> 00:39:06.566
out of proportion that he looked like some

903
00:39:06.566 --> 00:39:07.804
strange creature.

904
00:39:08.484 --> 00:39:09.906
Literally out to here.

905
00:39:11.306 --> 00:39:13.653
And, blood all over his face,

906
00:39:13.653 --> 00:39:16.023
he just looked like a piece of raw meat that

907
00:39:16.023 --> 00:39:17.833
had just been slaughtered.

908
00:39:20.263 --> 00:39:22.023
He was still conscious,

909
00:39:22.023 --> 00:39:23.202
of course they couldn't give 'em anything

910
00:39:23.202 --> 00:39:26.682
for the pain because it was trauma to the head.

911
00:39:26.682 --> 00:39:29.602
And, I...

912
00:39:31.750 --> 00:39:34.422
Almost immediately became extremely angry

913
00:39:34.422 --> 00:39:36.522
who would do this to my son?

914
00:39:36.522 --> 00:39:37.962
And he related the story then as to

915
00:39:37.962 --> 00:39:39.220
what happened, he said,

916
00:39:39.220 --> 00:39:40.962
"Dad, I simply got out of the car

917
00:39:40.962 --> 00:39:42.760
"and I turned around and wham.

918
00:39:44.620 --> 00:39:46.903
"Someone hit me, and apparently hit me more

919
00:39:46.903 --> 00:39:48.353
"than a couple of times."

920
00:39:50.055 --> 00:39:52.365
<v ->Richard was filled with a white hot anger</v>

921
00:39:52.365 --> 00:39:54.105
to get these guys,

922
00:39:54.105 --> 00:39:56.595
and he went looking for them all day Saturday

923
00:39:56.595 --> 00:39:58.253
and couldn't find them.

924
00:39:58.935 --> 00:40:00.345
Talked to people on the street,

925
00:40:00.345 --> 00:40:01.965
offered a reward, anything,

926
00:40:01.965 --> 00:40:05.085
he said, "I was going to break their kneecaps first,

927
00:40:05.085 --> 00:40:07.943
"before I gave them to the police."

928
00:40:08.475 --> 00:40:11.715
I think that would be a natural reaction for anyone.

929
00:40:11.715 --> 00:40:13.875
But the following day,

930
00:40:13.875 --> 00:40:16.573
he went to church with the baseball bat

931
00:40:16.573 --> 00:40:17.923
in his car.

932
00:40:17.923 --> 00:40:21.595
<v ->Wouldn't you know the homily that day was on forgiveness.</v>

933
00:40:24.135 --> 00:40:25.703
And, I...

934
00:40:27.703 --> 00:40:29.893
I still get a little choked up about it,

935
00:40:29.893 --> 00:40:33.203
but in my pew...

936
00:40:35.625 --> 00:40:36.985
I uh...

937
00:40:38.085 --> 00:40:41.263
Made a conscious decision

938
00:40:41.263 --> 00:40:43.005
to forgive those people,

939
00:40:43.005 --> 00:40:45.715
whoever they were, and uh...

940
00:40:47.715 --> 00:40:49.225
Not to pursue

941
00:40:50.773 --> 00:40:53.934
the vindictive type of behavior that I was.

942
00:40:53.934 --> 00:40:55.102
And while I was sitting there,

943
00:40:55.102 --> 00:40:59.154
I recall that I had to forgive those people too

944
00:40:59.154 --> 00:41:01.672
because I couldn't pray for my son's healing

945
00:41:03.542 --> 00:41:07.072
if I held something against someone else.

946
00:41:07.072 --> 00:41:09.482
So, I forgave, and...

947
00:41:10.912 --> 00:41:13.241
I prayed for my son's healing.

948
00:41:14.789 --> 00:41:18.629
And, I asked the Lord to take it from my memory,

949
00:41:18.629 --> 00:41:20.679
I mean the bad feelings.

950
00:41:21.361 --> 00:41:22.601
And he did.

951
00:41:22.921 --> 00:41:24.071
Anyway I went to...

952
00:41:25.079 --> 00:41:27.719
I went to the hospital that morning

953
00:41:27.719 --> 00:41:30.749
and upon exiting the elevator,

954
00:41:30.749 --> 00:41:32.159
one of the nurses spotted me

955
00:41:32.159 --> 00:41:33.769
and said, "Mr. Musielak, it's your son."

956
00:41:33.769 --> 00:41:34.697
<v Voiceover>We can't explain it,</v>

957
00:41:34.697 --> 00:41:36.229
we don't know how it happened.

958
00:41:36.229 --> 00:41:38.989
<v ->And I didn't remember exactly how I took that,</v>

959
00:41:38.989 --> 00:41:42.107
but I kinda trotted the rest of the way

960
00:41:42.107 --> 00:41:44.027
to the room.

961
00:41:44.027 --> 00:41:46.757
There I saw Paul, the swelling had gone down

962
00:41:46.757 --> 00:41:49.607
and he had opened his eyes.

963
00:41:49.607 --> 00:41:51.499
By this time of course a lot of the blood

964
00:41:51.499 --> 00:41:53.599
was already cleaned up off of his face and such,

965
00:41:53.599 --> 00:41:57.199
but I mean in and of itself

966
00:41:57.199 --> 00:42:00.079
it was like a miracle that he was actually

967
00:42:00.079 --> 00:42:03.409
able to open his eyes and the swelling had gone down.

968
00:42:03.409 --> 00:42:07.157
So then on Monday, we went back to the hospital

969
00:42:09.837 --> 00:42:11.399
to take Paul home.

970
00:42:12.559 --> 00:42:14.729
And, were amazed really.

971
00:42:15.979 --> 00:42:20.009
In seeing Paul with only bloodshot eyes.

972
00:42:21.437 --> 00:42:24.349
Not a contusion, not any evidence of

973
00:42:24.349 --> 00:42:26.569
any scratch or harm or beating at all.

974
00:42:27.686 --> 00:42:29.456
The swelling was completely gone down,

975
00:42:29.456 --> 00:42:31.294
he was in fine spirits.

976
00:42:31.857 --> 00:42:34.406
Later I found the report, the doctor's report

977
00:42:34.406 --> 00:42:38.126
about the exit x-ray of Paul.

978
00:42:38.126 --> 00:42:42.834
And when on Saturday there was a fractured skull,

979
00:42:42.834 --> 00:42:45.026
evidence of a fractured skull by x-ray.

980
00:42:45.026 --> 00:42:47.216
On Monday there was no evidence

981
00:42:47.216 --> 00:42:48.694
of any fracture at all.

982
00:42:49.314 --> 00:42:52.436
<v ->Most people focus on Paul,</v>

983
00:42:52.436 --> 00:42:56.036
and the marvelous restoration of Paul's face.

984
00:42:56.036 --> 00:42:58.194
Which of course is a miracle.

985
00:42:58.194 --> 00:43:00.026
But I would have a tendency to think that

986
00:43:00.026 --> 00:43:04.086
the other miracle was the healing of Richard's heart.

987
00:43:04.764 --> 00:43:07.536
On faith, he finally was able to

988
00:43:09.273 --> 00:43:11.851
just throw away his baseball bat and his plans

989
00:43:11.851 --> 00:43:14.503
for revenge, and...

990
00:43:15.693 --> 00:43:18.003
After that, his miracle happened.

991
00:43:18.003 --> 00:43:23.003
(gentle piano)

992
00:43:24.303 --> 00:43:26.403
<v Voiceover>A miracle is something that appears</v>

993
00:43:26.403 --> 00:43:29.284
to be unexplainable by the laws of nature,

994
00:43:29.284 --> 00:43:32.253
and so it thought to be supernatural in origin.

995
00:43:32.253 --> 00:43:33.881
Or, an act of God.

996
00:43:34.473 --> 00:43:36.273
The stories we just heard speak of

997
00:43:36.273 --> 00:43:38.523
profound and life-changing events,

998
00:43:38.523 --> 00:43:40.653
and phenomenal experiences

999
00:43:40.653 --> 00:43:43.901
that appear to be unexplainable by the laws of nature.

1000
00:43:44.461 --> 00:43:45.901
For the people who live them,

1001
00:43:45.901 --> 00:43:47.131
they are quite simply

1002
00:43:47.131 --> 00:43:49.993
their own personal stories of miracles.

1003
00:43:52.083 --> 00:43:54.301
<v ->The thing that we have to understand is that</v>

1004
00:43:54.301 --> 00:43:56.583
most of us have been brought up to think

1005
00:43:56.583 --> 00:43:59.191
in terms of reason,

1006
00:44:00.398 --> 00:44:03.790
rationality, to look at things philosophically

1007
00:44:03.790 --> 00:44:06.190
rather than theologically,

1008
00:44:06.190 --> 00:44:08.428
and while both philosophy and theology

1009
00:44:09.778 --> 00:44:11.629
will deal with some of the same questions

1010
00:44:11.629 --> 00:44:13.579
and the same issues, their starting point

1011
00:44:13.579 --> 00:44:15.169
is entirely different.

1012
00:44:15.169 --> 00:44:17.329
Philosophy begins with reason,

1013
00:44:17.329 --> 00:44:20.357
theology begins with faith.

1014
00:44:20.357 --> 00:44:21.920
Faith doesn't require proof

1015
00:44:21.920 --> 00:44:23.969
or it wouldn't be faith.

1016
00:44:26.419 --> 00:44:28.789
<v ->So often in miracles</v>

1017
00:44:28.789 --> 00:44:30.329
we see that um...

1018
00:44:31.969 --> 00:44:33.529
Sometimes the power of prayer,

1019
00:44:33.529 --> 00:44:35.659
it's brought on by someone else,

1020
00:44:35.659 --> 00:44:37.877
and I think we forget that the power of prayer

1021
00:44:37.877 --> 00:44:41.149
is beautiful in that a lot of us can get together

1022
00:44:41.149 --> 00:44:42.989
and pray for one person.

1023
00:44:45.139 --> 00:44:47.667
<v ->For those who can live their life</v>

1024
00:44:48.448 --> 00:44:50.308
putting out unconditional love to all those

1025
00:44:50.308 --> 00:44:53.786
around them, that kind of agape love

1026
00:44:53.786 --> 00:44:57.866
and certainly living a life of loving God.

1027
00:44:59.013 --> 00:45:01.293
I think those people probably experience miracles,

1028
00:45:01.293 --> 00:45:04.053
little amazing coincidences all the time,

1029
00:45:04.053 --> 00:45:07.503
and I think the closer we get to that ideal,

1030
00:45:07.503 --> 00:45:09.945
the more likely we are to experience miracles.

1031
00:45:11.763 --> 00:45:13.295
<v ->People are looking for answers,</v>

1032
00:45:13.295 --> 00:45:16.113
I think in the last couple decades

1033
00:45:16.113 --> 00:45:18.063
we thought science really was gonna be able to

1034
00:45:18.063 --> 00:45:19.895
provide us with answers, and we're gonna find cures

1035
00:45:19.895 --> 00:45:21.725
for all these diseases that we're really gonna

1036
00:45:21.725 --> 00:45:23.825
understand how the physical world operates,

1037
00:45:23.825 --> 00:45:25.983
and now we're not so sure if science can provide

1038
00:45:25.983 --> 00:45:27.635
those answers, so we're looking for other places of

1039
00:45:27.635 --> 00:45:29.615
how we might try better to understand

1040
00:45:29.615 --> 00:45:31.473
what the world is like,

1041
00:45:31.473 --> 00:45:34.475
and how cures can be affected.

1042
00:45:34.475 --> 00:45:36.483
And religion is providing a certain amount

1043
00:45:36.483 --> 00:45:38.252
of answers and people are finding miracles

1044
00:45:38.252 --> 00:45:39.814
or things that strike them as miracles

1045
00:45:39.814 --> 00:45:41.790
